The Water and Sanitation Department is again appealing to all South Africans to use water sparingly. JOHANNESBURG - The Water and Sanitation Departmentis again appealing to all South Africans to use water sparingly. Most of the country's dams remain under pressure due to the drought. The departments Sputnik Ratau, says levels haven't rebounded adequately enough following recent rains. The rains that have fallen over the last few days, although being welcomed, have not really made a dent on the dam levels as they are and therefore we are still wishing to put it out to people that the dam levels are still low.